[zero_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 27/100 done id=mmlu_validation_393 prediction='Let\'s analyze each statement one by one:\n\nI. "The committee chairpersons always belong to the majority party."\n- This statement is incorrect because it suggests that all committee chairs are from the same party, which is not true. There can be multiple party affiliations among committee chairs.\n\nII. "Seats on each committee are divided between the two major parties in exact proportion to the parties\' representation in Congress."\n- This statement is correct. According to the Constitution, each state has two representatives per member of Congress (one from each political party), so seats on each committee are indeed divided equally between the two major parties.\n\nIII. "They recommend whether Congress should pass various pieces of legislation, and those recommendations are always approved by the full congressional body."\n- This statement is partially correct but incomplete. While committees do make recommendations, they do not have the power to approve them outright unless specifically authorized by Congress. Additionally, committees may also propose amendments or changes to laws, which could affect their approval status.\n\nIV. "When a committee vote results in a tie, the vice president casts the tie-breaking vote."\n- This statement is incorrect. In reality, when there is a tie, the person who was elected as the chairman of the committee casts the tie-breaking vote, not the vice' gold='A' correct=False
