[few_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 35/100 done id=mmlu_validation_466 prediction="To solve this problem, we need to analyze each equation given and determine if there's a relationship between \\(a\\), \\(b\\), and \\(c\\) that can help us find \\(|a+b+c|\\).\n\nGiven equations:\n1. \\(a(a+2b) = \\frac{104}{3}\\)\n2. \\(b(b+2c) = \\frac{7}{9}\\)\n3. \\(c(c+2a) = -7\\)\n\nFirst, let's rewrite these equations in a more manageable form:\n\nFrom the first equation:\n\\[a^2 + 2ab = \\frac{104}{3}\\]\nDivide both sides by 3:\n\\[a^2 + 2ab = \\frac{104}{3}\\]\n\nFrom the second equation:\n\\[b^2 + 2bc = \\frac{7}{9}\\]\nDivide both sides by 2:\n\\[b^2 + bc = \\frac{7}{18}\\]\n\nFrom the third equation:\n\\[c^2 + 2ca = -7\\]\nThis can be rewritten as:\n\\[c^2 + 2ca = -7\\]\nor equivalently:\n\\[c^2 +" gold='C' correct=False
