[few_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 36/100 done id=mmlu_validation_476 prediction="To find the value of \\(c\\) for which the tangent to the graph of \\(f(x) = e^x - x^2\\) is parallel to the secant line on the interval \\([0,1]\\), we need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Find the derivative of \\(f(x)\\):**\n   \\[\n   f'(x) = \\frac{d}{dx}(e^x - x^2) = e^x - 2x\n   \\]\n\n2. **Set up the equation for the slope of the tangent line:**\n   Since the tangent line is parallel to the secant line, their slopes must be equal at some point \\(x = c\\). Therefore,\n   \\[\n   f'(c) = 1\n   \\]\n   Substituting \\(c\\) into the derivative, we get:\n   \\[\n   e^c - 2c = 1\n   \\]\n\n3. **Solve for \\(c\\):**\n   We need to solve the equation \\(e^c - 2c = 1\\). This is a transcendental equation and typically requires numerical methods or graphical analysis to find its solution within the given range \\(0 < x < 1\\)." gold='B' correct=False
