[few_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 72/100 done id=mmlu_validation_1206 prediction='To determine the correct answer, we need to consider the nature of the statement and how it relates to the context of the case. The statement is:\n\n"you\'d better watch out. At a hockey game last week, the visiting fan put two guys in the hospital when they wouldn\'t shut up."\n\nThis statement is about the impact of the home fan\'s behavior on the visiting fan. It suggests that the home fan\'s actions were causing distress or discomfort to the visiting fan. This kind of statement can be considered a present sense impression, where the witness (the home fan) provides evidence of what the other party (the visiting fan) experienced based on their own experience.\n\nGiven this interpretation, the statement would most likely be admissible as a present sense impression rather than as hearsay. Therefore, the correct choice is:\n\n**B. admissible as a present sense impression.**' gold='A' correct=False
