[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 2/100 path 2/3 answer="First, let's calculate how far Tom travels on his first leg of the journey:\n\nHe covers 10 miles/hour * 4 hours = 40 miles\n\nNow, he will travel back from 1 to 4 PM, which is 3 hours:\n\nDistance for return trip = Speed * Time = 6 mph * 3 hours = 18 miles\n\nTotal distance traveled:\nFirst leg (1st half) + Second leg (return) = 40 miles + 18 miles = 58 miles\n\nTo find out how long it takes for the total trip (from 1 to 4 PM and back):\nTime taken = Total distance / Speed = 58 miles / 10 mph = 5.8 hours\n\nTherefore, it takes Tom 5.8 hours to complete the round trip."
