[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 3/100 path 1/3 answer='First, we find out how many kittens Patchy has by multiplying the number of kittens she already has (which was 7) by the number of kittens she has had so far (the triple). So Patchy has 7 * 3 = 21 kittens.\nNext, we add the 12 kittens Trixie has to what Patchy has to get the total number of kittens the Doubtfire family has. So there are 21 + 12 = 33 kittens in total.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 3/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 3/100 path 2/3 answer="First, let's find out how many kittens Patchy has. Since Patchy has had thrice the number of kittens as the total number of kittens they initially had, we can calculate it as follows:\nPatchy kittens = 3 times the number of adopted kittens\nSince 7 adopted kittens were made, we can assume there were also 7 kittens left over (the initial count minus the adopted ones).\nSo Patchy kittens = 3 * 7 kittens\n\nNow, let's calculate Trixie's kittens, which was already given as 12.\n\nTotal kittens = Patchy kittens + Trixie kittens\nTotal kittens = 3 * 7 kittens + 12 kittens\n\nNow, let's do the math:\n\nPatchy kittens = 3 * 7 = 21 kittens\n\nTrixie kittens = 12 kittens\n\nTotal kittens = 21 + 12 = 33 kittens\n\nTherefore, the Doubtfire family now has 33 kittens."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 3/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 3/100 path 3/3 answer="To find out how many kittens the Doubtfire family has now, we'll start by calculating the number of kittens each sister has received:\n\nPatchy (the first kitten) has had thrice the number of adopted kittens, so:\n\\[ \\text{Patchy's kittens} = 3 \\times 7 = 21 \\]\n\nTrixie (the second kitten) has had 12 kittens.\n\nNow, let's sum up all the kittens:\n\\[ \\text{Total kittens} = \\text{Patchy's kittens} + \\text{Trixie's kittens} = 21 + 12 = 33 \\]\n\nTherefore, the Doubtfire family now has 33 kittens."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 3/100 done id=gsm8k_test_54 prediction='First, we find out how many kittens Patchy has by multiplying the number of kittens she already has (which was 7) by the number of kittens she has had so far (the triple). So Patchy has 7 * 3 = 21 kittens.\nNext, we add the 12 kittens Trixie has to what Patchy has to get the total number of kittens the Doubtfire family has. So there are 21 + 12 = 33 kittens in total.' gold='40' correct=False vote_counts={'First, we find out how many kittens Patchy has by multiplying the number of kittens she already has (which was 7) by the number of kittens she has had so far (the triple). So Patchy has 7 * 3 = 21 kittens.\nNext, we add the 12 kittens Trixie has to what Patchy has to get the total number of kittens the Doubtfire family has. So there are 21 + 12 = 33 kittens in total.': 1, "First, let's find out how many kittens Patchy has. Since Patchy has had thrice the number of kittens as the total number of kittens they initially had, we can calculate it as follows:\nPatchy kittens = 3 times the number of adopted kittens\nSince 7 adopted kittens were made, we can assume there were also 7 kittens left over (the initial count minus the adopted ones).\nSo Patchy kittens = 3 * 7 kittens\n\nNow, let's calculate Trixie's kittens, which was already given as 12.\n\nTotal kittens = Patchy kittens + Trixie kittens\nTotal kittens = 3 * 7 kittens + 12 kittens\n\nNow, let's do the math:\n\nPatchy kittens = 3 * 7 = 21 kittens\n\nTrixie kittens = 12 kittens\n\nTotal kittens = 21 + 12 = 33 kittens\n\nTherefore, the Doubtfire family now has 33 kittens.": 1, "To find out how many kittens the Doubtfire family has now, we'll start by calculating the number of kittens each sister has received:\n\nPatchy (the first kitten) has had thrice the number of adopted kittens, so:\n\\[ \\text{Patchy's kittens} = 3 \\times 7 = 21 \\]\n\nTrixie (the second kitten) has had 12 kittens.\n\nNow, let's sum up all the kittens:\n\\[ \\text{Total kittens} = \\text{Patchy's kittens} + \\text{Trixie's kittens} = 21 + 12 = 33 \\]\n\nTherefore, the Doubtfire family now has 33 kittens.": 1}
