[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 4/100 path 2/3 answer="First, we calculate the total cost of the material plus the jeweler's work. This includes $500 (material) + $800 (jewelry) = $1300. Then, we apply the insurance fee of 10%. So, we calculate 10% of $1300, which is 0.10 * $1300 = $130. Finally, we subtract this insurance fee from the total cost to find out how much Janet paid: $1300 - $130 = $1170.\n\nTherefore, Janet paid $1170 for the brooch."
