[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 5/100 path 3/3 answer='First, we calculate how long Jim spent reading each day:\n\nHalf the time he spends watching TV: 2 hours / 2 = 1 hour\n\nSo, Jim reads for 1 hour each day. Since he does this 3 times a week, we can calculate his weekly reading time:\n\n1 hour/day × 3 days/week = 3 hours/week\n\nNow, we multiply this weekly reading time by the number of weeks:\n\n3 hours/week × 4 weeks = 12 hours\n\nTherefore, Jim spends a total of 12 hours on TV and reading over 4 weeks.'
