[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 6/100 path 2/3 answer="Let H be the number of copies Harald sold. According to the problem, Marilyn sold 10H copies. The total number of copies sold is H + 10H = 88,000. This simplifies to 11H = 88,000.\n\nTo find out how many copies Harald sold (H), we can divide both sides by 11:\n\n\\[ H = \\frac{88,000}{11} \\]\n\nNow let's calculate H:\n\\[ H = 8000 \\]\n\nSo, Harald sold 8000 copies of the record."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 6/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 6/100 path 3/3 answer="Let's denote Harald's sales as \\( H \\). According to the problem:\n\n1. Marilyn sold 10 times as many copies as Harald, so if Harald sold \\( H \\) copies, Marilyn sold \\( 10H \\) copies.\n2. Together, they sold 88,000 copies, so we can write the equation:\n   \\[\n   H + 10H = 88,000\n   \\]\n3. Simplifying the equation:\n   \\[\n   11H = 88,000\n   \\]\n4. Solving for \\( H \\):\n   \\[\n   H = \\frac{88,000}{11}\n   \\]\n\nNow, let's calculate Harald's sales using this formula."
