[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 9/100 path 2/3 answer='First, we calculate how many video games Bobby originally had before losing some. Since he started with 20 games and lost 5 right before the comparison was made, he ended up with \\(20 + 5 = 25\\) games. \n\nAccording to the problem, Bobby now has 5 fewer than 3 times as many video games as Brian did initially. So, if Brian had 20 games, Bobby has \\(3 \\times 20 - 5 = 60 - 5 = 55\\) games now.\n\nTherefore, Bobby has 55 video games.'
