[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 10/100 path 1/3 answer="To calculate how much Jordan would earn in one week, we first find out how many hours he spends playing video games each week:\nJordan plays for 2 hours every day, so in a week (7 days), it's 2 hours/day * 7 days/week = 14 hours.\n\nNext, we calculate how much he earns from his job:\nHe earns $10/hour, so in 14 hours, he earns 14 hours/day * $10/hour = $<<14*10=140>>140.\n\nFinally, we calculate his total earnings for the week:\nTotal weekly earnings = Earnings from gaming + Earnings from work\nEarnings from gaming = 14 hours * $2/hour\nEarnings from gaming = 14 * 2 = $<<14*2=28>>28\n\nSo, Jordan would earn $28 in one week if he spent all his video game time working."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 10/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 10/100 path 2/3 answer='First find out how much time Jordan spends playing video games each day: 2 hours/day × 7 days/week = <<2*7=14>>14 hours/day.\nThen calculate how much he earns from his gaming: 14 hours/day × $2/hour = <<14*2=28>>28 dollars/day.\nFinally, multiply his daily earnings by the number of weekdays in a week (assuming 5): 28 dollars/day × 5 days/week = <<28*5=140>>140 dollars/week.\nSo Jordan would earn 140 dollars in one week if he spent his video game time working instead.'
