[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 11/100 path 1/3 answer='First, we find out how many Lego sets there were:\n\nSet 1: 500 pieces\nSet 2: 3 times more than Set 1, so it would have 3 * 500 = 1500 pieces\n\nSet 3: 1/4 the number of Pieces from Set 2, so it would have 1500 / 4 = 375 pieces\n\nNow, adding them together:\n500 (Set 1) + 1500 (Set 2) + 375 (Set 3) = 2375 pieces\n\nJohnny picked up all 2375 Legos.'
