[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 11/100 path 2/3 answer="First, let's determine how many Lego sets Johnny picked up:\n\n- One Lego set was 500 pieces.\n- Another set with three times the pieces would have \\( 500 \\times 3 = 1500 \\) pieces.\n- A third set with one-fourth the pieces would have \\( 1500 \\div 4 = 375 \\) pieces.\n\nNow we add these together:\n\\( 500 + 1500 + 375 = 2375 \\)\n\nJohnny picked up 2375 Legos."
