[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 start id=gsm8k_test_161
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 path 1/3 answer="Let's break down the problem step-by-step:\n\n1) **Starfish**: Anakin caught 10 starfish and Locsin caught 5 fewer. So, Anakin caught 10 - 5 = 5 starfish.\n   Locsin caught 3 fewer sea horses than Anakin. Since Anakin had 6 sea horses, Locsin caught 6 - 3 = 3 sea horses.\n\n2) **Clownfish**: Anakin caught 3 clownfish and Locsin caught 2 more. Since Anakin had 3 clownfish, Locsin caught 3 + 2 = 5 clownfish.\n\nNow, let's sum up all the fish they caught:\n- Starfish: 5 (Anakin) + 5 (Locsin) = 10 stars\n- Sea horses: 6 (Anakin) + 3 (Locsin) = 9 sea horses\n- Clownfish: 3 (Anakin) + 5 (Locsin) = 8 clownfish\n\nTherefore, the total number of fish they caught together is 10 + 9 + 8 = 27 fish."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 path 2/3 answer="First, let's calculate how many fish Locsin caught:\nLocsin caught 5 fewer starfish than Anakin: 10 - 5 = 5 starfish\nLocsin caught 3 fewer sea horses than Anakin: 6 - 3 = 3 sea horses\nLocsin caught 2 more clownfish than Anakin: 3 + 2 = 5 clownfish\n\nNow we can find out the total number of fish they caught together:\nTotal fish = Starfish + Sea horses + Clownfish\nTotal fish = 10 (Anakin) + 3 (Locsin, starfish) + 5 (Locsin, sea horses)\nTotal fish = 18\n\nSo, they managed to catch a total of 18 fish."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 path 3/3 answer="First, let's determine how many sea horses and clownfish Anakin caught:\nAnakin caught 6 sea horses and 3 clownfish.\nLocsin caught 5 fewer starfish than Anakin, which is 10 stars (since 10 > 6) and 3 fewer sea horses than Anakin, which is 9 seas (since 3 < 6).\nLocsin also caught 2 more clownfish than Anakin, which is 5 more (since 3 + 2).\n\nNow, we'll sum up all the fish caught by both Anakin and Locsin:\n\nAnakin's total fish: 6 (sea horses) + 3 (clownfish) + 10 (starfish) = 19 fish\nLocsin's total fish: 10 (starfish) + 9 (sea horses) + 5 (clownfish) + 3 (sea horses) = 27 fish\n\nTogether, they caught 19 + 27 = 46 fish."
