[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 13/100 path 2/3 answer="Let's break down the information given:\n\n1. Dolls cost as much as 3 action figures: Since each action figure costs $5, dolls would also cost $15.\n2. Each red car costs $4.\n3. We don't know how many red cars there are yet, but we do know the total number of toys (red cars + action figures), which is 5 + 3 = 8.\n\nNow, let's calculate the value of all the toys combined:\n- Dolls: $15\n- Red cars: 5 × $4 = $20\n- Action figures: 3 × $5 = $15\n\nTo find the total value of all toys, we simply add these amounts together:\nTotal value = Value of dolls + Value of red cars + Value of action figures\nTotal value = $15 + $20 + $15\nTotal value = $50\n\nTherefore, all toys together are worth $50."
