[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 15/100 path 1/3 answer="First, we calculate the total cost of the tickets:\n\\[ \\text{Total ticket cost} = \\$20.25 \\]\n\nNext, we find out how much they spent on food:\n\\[ \\text{Food cost} = \\text{Total ticket cost} - \\$4.50 = \\$20.25 - \\$4.50 = \\$\\$15.75 \\]\n\nThen, we know they bought two rides at $33 each:\n\\[ \\text{Ride cost} = 2 \\times \\$33 = \\$\\$66 \\]\n\nNow, let's sum up all these expenses:\n\\[ \\text{Total expense} = \\text{Tickets} + \\text{Food} + \\text{Rides} = \\$20.25 + \\$15.75 + \\$66 = \\$\\$102.00 \\]\n\nFinally, we divide the total expense by the number of people to find out how much each person should contribute:\n\\[ \\text{Each person's contribution} = \\frac{\\$102.00}{3} = \\$\\boxed{34.00} \\]"
