[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 1/3 answer="First, let's find out how many pounds of insects all the ducks would consume together weekly. Each duck eats 3.5 pounds, so:\n\n10 ducks * 3.5 pounds/duck = 35 pounds\n\nNow, since there are 7 days in a week, we divide the weekly consumption by 7 to get the daily consumption:\n\n35 pounds / 7 days = 5 pounds/day\n\nSo, the ducks would need 5 pounds of insects per day."
