[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 18/100 path 3/3 answer="To calculate the total number of kilometers Michael rode, we can break down his rides into two parts:\n\n1. First part (weeks 1-4):\n   - He rode the bike 5 times a week for 25 km each time.\n   - Total distance for these rides: 5 times/week * 25 km/time = 125 km/week\n   - For 4 weeks: 125 km/week * 4 weeks = 500 km\n\n2. Second part (weeks 5-6):\n   - He now rides the bike 2 times a week for 60 km each time.\n   - Total distance for these rides: 2 times/week * 60 km/time = 120 km/week\n   - For 3 weeks: 120 km/week * 3 weeks = 360 km\n\nNow, let's sum up the total distance:\n\nTotal distance = 500 km + 360 km = 860 km\n\nSo, Michael rode a total of 860 kilometers."
