[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 start id=gsm8k_test_228
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 1/3 answer="To determine how long it takes for both Kalinda and her mom to complete the puzzle together, we first calculate their individual rates:\n\nKalinda adds 4 pieces per minute, so her rate is \\( \\frac{4}{60} = \\frac{1}{15} \\) pieces per minute.\n\nHer mom adds half as many pieces per minute as Kalinda, so her mom's rate is \\( \\frac{1}{15} \\times \\frac{1}{2} = \\frac{1}{30} \\) pieces per minute.\n\nTogether, they add \\( \\frac{1}{15} + \\frac{1}{30} \\) pieces per minute.\n\nTo find the combined rate, we convert everything to have a common denominator (which is 30):\n\n\\( \\frac{2}{30} + \\frac{1}{30} = \\frac{3}{30} = \\frac{1}{10} \\)\n\nSo, together they add \\( \\frac{1}{10} \\) pieces per minute.\n\nThey need to solve the equation \\( \\frac{1}{10} t = 360 \\), where \\( t \\) is the number of minutes.\n\nSolving for \\( t \\):\n\n\\( t = 360 \\times 10 = 3600 \\)\n\nSince there are 60 minutes in an hour, we convert the total time needed from minutes to hours:\n\n\\( 3600 \\text{ minutes} \\div 60 \\text{ minutes/hour} = 60 \\text{ hours} \\)\n\nTherefore, it will take them 60 hours to complete the puzzle when working together at their respective rates."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 2/3 answer="First, we calculate how many pieces Kalinda works on the puzzle per minute:\nKalinda + Mom's rate = 360 pieces / 60 mins = 6 pieces per minute\n\nNext, we calculate the number of pieces Mom can do in one minute:\nMom's rate = 6 pieces per minute / 2 = 3 pieces per minute\n\nNow, we find out how many pieces they need to add together:\nTotal needed = 360 pieces - 6 pieces = 354 pieces\n\nSince Mom can add 3 pieces per minute, we can determine how many minutes it will take her to add all 354 pieces:\nTime taken = Total needed / Mom's rate = 354 pieces / 3 pieces per minute = 118 minutes\n\nTo convert minutes to hours:\nTime in hours = 118 minutes / 60 minutes per hour = 1 hour and 58 minutes\n\nSo, it would take them **1 hour and 58 minutes** to complete the puzzle."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 3/3 answer='To determine how long it will take to complete the puzzle, we first need to calculate their combined rate of adding pieces per minute.\n\nKalinda adds 4 pieces per minute.\nHer mom adds half as many pieces per minute as Kalinda, so her mom adds \\( \\frac{4}{2} = 2 \\) pieces per minute.\n\nTogether, they add:\n\\[ 4 + 2 = 6 \\text{ pieces per minute} \\]\n\nThe puzzle requires 360 pieces. Therefore, the time required to complete the puzzle at their combined rate is:\n\\[ \\frac{360 \\text{ pieces}}{6 \\text{ pieces per minute}} = 60 \\text{ minutes} \\]\n\nConverting minutes to hours:\n\\[ \\frac{60 \\text{ minutes}}{60 \\text{ minutes/hour}} = 1 \\text{ hour} \\]\n\nThus, it will take them **1 hour** to complete the puzzle.'
