[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 21/100 start id=gsm8k_test_255
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 21/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 21/100 path 1/3 answer='First, calculate the total number of cows before Mr. Sylas buys the additional 40 cows:\nTotal cows = Number of stalls × Cows per stall = 10 × 20 = 200\n\nThen, determine how many cows are given to each of the original stalls:\nCows per stall = Total cows ÷ Stalls = 200 ÷ 10 = 20\n\nSince he gives 40 cows (40 × 2) to each stall, we can find out how many cows are in each original stall:\nOriginal cows per stall = Total cows ÷ Stalls = 200 ÷ 10 = 20\n\nMr. Sylas then divides these 40 cows equally among the 20 original stalls, so each stall gets:\nStall share of 40 cows = 40 ÷ 20 = 2 cows\n\nNow, since each stall still gets 2 cows, we want to know how many cows would be in 8 of those stalls:\nCows in 8 stalls = Stall share × Stalls = 2 × 8 = 16\n\nTherefore, there will be 16 cows in 8 of the stalls.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 21/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 21/100 path 2/3 answer="To determine how many cows are in 8 of the stalls after the purchase, we'll follow these steps:\n\n1. **Initial Setup**: \n   - Total number of stalls: 10\n   - Number of cows per stall initially: 20\n\n2. **Total Initial Cows**:\n   \\[\n   10 \\text{ stalls} \\times 20 \\text{ cows/stall} = 200 \\text{ cows}\n   \\]\n\n3. **New Cows Purchase**:\n   - New total number of cows to be divided: \\( 200 + 40 = 240 \\)\n   - Each stall will get an equal number of new cows:\n     \\[\n     \\frac{240}{10 \\text{ stalls}} = 24 \\text{ cows/stall}\n     \\]\n   \n4. **Number of Stalls with New Cows**:\n   - We want to find out how many cows are in 8 of these stalls.\n\n5. **Cows in One Stall**:\n   - Since each stall receives 24 cows from the new purchase, we divide the new total number of cows by the number of stalls:\n     \\[\n     \\frac{240 \\text{ cows}}{10 \\text{ stalls}} = 24 \\text{ cows/stall}\n     \\]\n\n6. **Calculate Cows in 8 Stalls**:\n   - Multiply the number of cows per stall by 8:\n     \\[\n     24 \\text{ cows/stall} \\times 8 \\text{ stalls} = 192 \\text{ cows}\n     \\]\n\nThus, the number of cows in 8 of the stalls is \\( \\boxed{192} \\)."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 21/100 path 3/3 start
