  10 \\text{ stalls} \\times 20 \\text{ cows/stall} = 200 \\text{ cows}\n   \\]\n\n3. **New Cows Purchase**:\n   - New total number of cows to be divided: \\( 200 + 40 = 240 \\)\n   - Each stall will get an equal number of new cows:\n     \\[\n     \\frac{240}{10 \\text{ stalls}} = 24 \\text{ cows/stall}\n     \\]\n   \n4. **Number of Stalls with New Cows**:\n   - We want to find out how many cows are in 8 of these stalls.\n\n5. **Cows in One Stall**:\n   - Since each stall receives 24 cows from the new purchase, we divide the new total number of cows by the number of stalls:\n     \\[\n     \\frac{240 \\text{ cows}}{10 \\text{ stalls}} = 24 \\text{ cows/stall}\n     \\]\n\n6. **Calculate Cows in 8 Stalls**:\n   - Multiply the number of cows per stall by 8:\n     \\[\n     24 \\text{ cows/stall} \\times 8 \\text{ stalls} = 192 \\text{ cows}\n     \\]\n\nThus, the number of cows in 8 of the stalls is \\( \\boxed{192} \\).": 1, '160': 1}
