[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 23/100 path 3/3 answer='First, we calculate the total time Susan spends on the task:\n- 8 a.m. to 9 a.m. (1 hour) + 9 a.m. to 11 a.m. (2 hours)\nTotal time = 1 + 2 = 3 hours\n\nNext, we determine the number of 10-minute intervals in the total work time:\nNumber of intervals = Total time / 10 minutes per interval\nNumber of intervals = 3 hours / 10 minutes per interval\nConvert the total time into minutes to avoid confusion with seconds:\nTotal time in minutes = 3 hours * 60 minutes/hour = 180 minutes\nNumber of intervals = 180 minutes / 10 minutes per interval\nNumber of intervals = 18\nNow, multiply the number of intervals by the earnings per interval to find the total earnings:\nTotal earnings = Number of intervals * Earnings per interval\nTotal earnings = 18 * $5 per interval\nTotal earnings = $90\nTherefore, Susan earns $90 for the online task.'
