[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 25/100 path 1/3 answer="Let's break it down step-by-step:\n\n1. Initially, at the first bus stop, there were 5 people on the bus.\n2. At the second bus stop, 7 people got off and 8 more got on, so there would have been \\(5 + 7 + 8 = 20\\) people on the bus at that time.\n3. We know that at the third bus stop, there was a total of 20 people heading to the next stop.\n\nSince we already accounted for all the people getting on and off the bus during the first two stops, we don't need to worry about additional people arriving or leaving the terminal. Therefore, the number of people who got on the bus at the terminal is simply the total number of people at the third stop, which is 20."
