[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 26/100 path 1/3 answer="Robert should choose the offer from Furniture United because it offers a lower total upfront cost compared to Cozy Homes. \n\nFirst, let's calculate the total cost for both offers:\n\nFor Furniture United:\n- Advance payment: $1,350\n- Monthly payments: $350 each (for 6 months)\nTotal for Furniture United = $1,350 + ($350 x 6) = $1,350 + $2,100 = $3,450\n\nFor Cozy Homes:\n- Advance payment: $1,100\n- Monthly payments: $250 each (for 9 months)\nTotal for Cozy Homes = $1,100 + ($250 x 9) = $1,100 + $2,250 = $3,350\n\nNow we can find the difference between the two offers:\nDifference = Total for Furniture United - Total for Cozy Homes\nDifference = $3,450 - $3,350 = $100\n\nSo the cost difference between the two offers is $100."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 26/100 path 2/3 start
