[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 28/100 path 1/3 answer="Let's break it down step-by-step:\n\n1. **Yoga Class**: This activity lasts 1 hour.\n   - Total time for yoga class = 1 hour\n\n2. **Cooking Class**: This activity lasts 3 times as long as the yoga class.\n   - Time for cooking class = 1 hour * 3 = 3 hours\n\n3. **Cheese-Tasting Event**: This activity lasts 0.5 hours (half an hour).\n   - Time for cheese tasting event = 0.5 hours\n\n4. **Museum Tour**: This activity lasts half as long as the cooking class.\n   - Time for museum tour = 3 hours / 2 = 1.5 hours\n\n5. **Errands**: This activity lasts 2 hours.\n   - Total time for after-work activities = 1 + 3 + 0.5 + 1.5 + 2 = 7.5 hours\n\nTherefore, the total time Peyton's after-work activities will take is **7.5** hours."
