[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 31/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 31/100 path 3/3 answer="To find out how many letters there are in Indras' and her sister's names combined, let's break down the problem step-by-step:\n\n1. **Indras' Name:** Indras has 6 letters in her name.\n2. **Sister's Name:** According to the question, her sister's name has 4 more letters than half of the letters in Indras' name.\n\nFirst, calculate half of Indras' name:\n\\[\n\\text{Half} = \\frac{\\text{Number of Letters in Indras' Name}}{2}\n\\]\n\\[\n\\text{Half} = \\frac{6}{2} = 3\n\\]\n\nThen, calculate the number of letters in the sister's name:\n\\[\n\\text{Letter Count in Sister's Name} = \\text{Half} + 4\n\\]\n\\[\n\\text{Letter Count in Sister's Name} = 3 + 4 = 7\n\\]\n\nNow, add the letters from both names together:\n\\[\n\\text{Total Number of Letters} = \\text{Letters in Indras' Name} + \\text{Letters in Sister's Name}\n\\]\n\\[\n\\text{Total Number of Letters} = 6 + 7 = 13\n\\]\n\nSo, Indras and her sister's combined total number of letters is 13."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 31/100 done id=gsm8k_test_429 prediction='13' gold='13' correct=True vote_counts={'13': 2, "To find out how many letters there are in Indras' and her sister's names combined, let's break down the problem step-by-step:\n\n1. **Indras' Name:** Indras has 6 letters in her name.\n2. **Sister's Name:** According to the question, her sister's name has 4 more letters than half of the letters in Indras' name.\n\nFirst, calculate half of Indras' name:\n\\[\n\\text{Half} = \\frac{\\text{Number of Letters in Indras' Name}}{2}\n\\]\n\\[\n\\text{Half} = \\frac{6}{2} = 3\n\\]\n\nThen, calculate the number of letters in the sister's name:\n\\[\n\\text{Letter Count in Sister's Name} = \\text{Half} + 4\n\\]\n\\[\n\\text{Letter Count in Sister's Name} = 3 + 4 = 7\n\\]\n\nNow, add the letters from both names together:\n\\[\n\\text{Total Number of Letters} = \\text{Letters in Indras' Name} + \\text{Letters in Sister's Name}\n\\]\n\\[\n\\text{Total Number of Letters} = 6 + 7 = 13\n\\]\n\nSo, Indras and her sister's combined total number of letters is 13.": 1}
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 start id=gsm8k_test_432
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 1/3 answer='First, we calculate how many dragons each person slew:\n- Prince Thaddeus: 100 dragons\n- Prince Arthur: Three quarters of what he slew by Prince Thaddeus, so \\( \\frac{3}{4} \\times 100 = 75 \\) dragons\n- Prince Walter: Twice as many as Prince Arthur, so \\( 2 \\times 75 = 150 \\) dragons\n- Prince Bruce: One-fifth of what he slew by Prince Walter, so \\( \\frac{1}{5} \\times 150 = 30 \\) dragons\n\nTherefore, Prince Bruce has slayed 30 dragons.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 2/3 answer="First, let's calculate how many dragons each person killed:\n- Prince Thaddeus killed 100 dragons.\n- Prince Arthur, who used a spear, killed three quarters as many as Thaddeus, so he killed 100 * (3/4) = 75 dragons.\n- Prince Walter, who used a rusty iron axe, killed twice as many as Arthur, so he killed 75 * 2 = 150 dragons.\n- Prince Bruce, who forgot his sword and had to use a nail file instead, killed one-fifth as many as Walter, so he killed 150 / (5/7) = 150 * (7/5) = 210 dragons.\n\nTherefore, Prince Bruce has slain 210 dragons."
