Perimeter} = 2 \\times (3 + 120) \\text{ yds} = 2 \\times 123 \\text{ yds} = 246 \\text{ yds} \\]\n\nTherefore, the perimeter of Billie's rectangular bedroom is 246 yards.": 1, '246': 1}
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 35/100 start id=gsm8k_test_447
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 35/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 35/100 path 1/3 answer="To determine how many more points Joey wins than Marcy, we need to calculate their total score after their turns and then find the difference between these totals.\n\nFirst, let's calculate Joey's score:\nJoey starts with 214 points. After scoring 26 points, his total becomes \\(214 + 26\\).\n\nNext, let's calculate Marcy's score:\nMarcy starts with 225 points. After scoring 10 points, her total becomes \\(225 + 10\\).\n\nNow, we'll find the difference between Marcy's total score and Joey's total score:\n\n\\[ \\text{Difference} = (\\text{Marcy's total score}) - (\\text{Joey's total score}) \\]\n\nSubstituting the values:\n\n\\[ \\text{Difference} = (225 + 10) - (214 + 26) \\]\n\\[ \\text{Difference} = 235 - 240 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Difference} = -5 \\]\n\nSo, Joey is losing 5 points compared to Marcy. The negative value indicates that Joey loses more than Marcy."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 35/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 35/100 path 2/3 answer="First, calculate Joey's score before Marcy's contribution: \\(214 + 26 = 240\\) points.\nThen, subtract Marcy's initial score from Joey's total: \\(240 - 225 = 15\\) points.\nJoey is now 15 points ahead of Marcy.\n\nAnswer: Joey is now winning by \\( \\boxed{15} \\) points."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 35/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 35/100 path 3/3 answer="To determine by how many points Joey is winning, we first calculate the net increase in points:\nJoey starts with 214 points and gets 26 back, so:\n\\[ \\text{Net Increase} = 214 - 26 = 188 \\]\n\nNext, we look at Marcy's points. We know Marcy started with 225 points and scored 10 more, so:\n\\[ \\text{Final Points} = 225 + 10 = 235 \\]\n\nNow, we find out by how many points Joey is winning by subtracting Marcy's final score from Joey's net increase:\n\\[ \\text{Points Difference} = 188 - 235 = -47 \\]\nSince Joey lost 47 points, he is losing by 47 points compared to Marcy. Therefore, the correct answer is:\n\\[ \\boxed{-47} \\]"
