[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 36/100 path 3/3 answer='First, we calculate the number of crayon pieces from the six packets with eight pieces:\n\\[ 6 \\times 8 = 48 \\]\n\nNext, we calculate the number of crayon pieces from the four packets with sixteen pieces:\n\\[ 4 \\times 16 = 64 \\]\n\nNow, we add these two amounts together to find the total number of crayon pieces:\n\\[ 48 + 64 = 112 \\]\n\nTherefore, Beatrice bought a total of 112 crayon pieces.'
