[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 37/100 path 2/3 answer='First, calculate the original price per balloon using the initial cost:\n\\[ \\text{Original price} = \\frac{\\$900}{20\\text{ balloons}} = \\$45/\\text{balloon} \\]\n\nThen, determine the new price per balloon after the increase:\n\\[ \\text{New price} = \\$45 + \\$20 = \\$65/\\text{balloon} \\]\n\nNow, calculate the total cost for 170 balloons at the new rate:\n\\[ \\text{Total cost} = 170\\text{ balloons} \\times \\$65/\\text{balloon} = \\$11,050 \\]\n\nBentley paid $\\boxed{11050}$ dollars to fill 170 balloons.'
