[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 38/100 path 3/3 answer='Katelyn initially saw 50 fairies. One of her friends saw half as many, so they saw 50 / 2 = 25 fairies. These 25 fairies joined the initial 50 fairies that Katelyn had seen, making it 25 + 50 = 75 fairies. \n\nTen minutes later, 30 fairies flew away, leaving 75 - 30 = 45 fairies.\n\nSo, the number of fairies remaining after ten minutes is 45.'
