[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 44/100 path 2/3 answer="First, let's calculate how many videos Emma made in total from January to March:\n\nJanuary: 18 vlogs\nFebruary: 21 vlogs\nMarch: 15 vlogs\n\nTotal: 18 + 21 + 15 = 54 vlogs\n\nNow, we know that Emma makes 72 vlogs per month. To find out how many more videos she needs to make to reach 72, subtract the number of videos she already made:\n\n72 (total desired) - 54 (already made) = 18 vlogs needed\n\nTherefore, Emma should make 18 additional vlogs to complete her goal of making 72 vlogs per month."
