total number of letters written:\n\\[52 + 13 + 26 = 91\\]\n\nElise has written a total of 91 letters.": 1, 'Elise starts with the letter A. She writes down all 26 letters of the alphabet in sequence until she has covered them all. Then, she writes half of the remaining letters (i.e., 13) once each time she finishes writing one letter each time.\n\nSo, before re-writing, she wrote:\n\\[ 26 \\]\n\nAfter she finished writing, she added back half of the remaining letters:\n\\[ 13 + 13 = 26 \\]\n\nTo find out how many letters she wrote in total, we can sum up both parts:\n\\[ 26 (letters written initially) + 26 (letters written twice) = 52 \\]\n\nTherefore, Elise has written a total of 52 letters.': 1, '16': 1}
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 start id=gsm8k_test_548
