[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 path 1/3 answer="To find Mark's initial weight, we can work backwards from his final weight. Since each month he loses 10 pounds, we need to subtract 10 pounds three times (because there were 3 months) to get back to his starting point of 70 pounds. \n\nSo, Mark's initial weight = Final weight - (Weight lost per month × Number of months)\n\nLet's calculate it:\n\nInitial weight = 70 - (10 × 3)\nInitial weight = 70 - 30\nInitial weight = 40\n\nTherefore, Mark's initial weight was 40 pounds."
