[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 49/100 path 1/3 answer="To calculate Antonella's earnings, we'll break down the sales into two parts:\n1. The first part includes selling $1000 worth of goods at a 30% commission rate.\n2. The second part includes selling over $1000 worth of goods at an additional 10% commission rate.\n\nFirst, let's calculate the earnings from the $1000 sale:\n\\[ \\text{Commission} = \\$1000 \\times 30\\% = \\$1000 \\times 0.30 = \\$300 \\]\n\nNext, let's calculate the earnings from the over $1000 sales:\n\\[ \\text{Over $1000 sales} = \\$2500 - \\$1000 = \\$1500 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Commission from over } \\$1000 \\text{ sales} = \\$1500 \\times 10\\% = \\$1500 \\times 0.10 = \\$150 \\]\n\nNow, let's sum up both parts to find Antonella's total earnings:\n\\[ \\text{Total earnings} = \\$300 + \\$150 = \\$450 \\]\n\nTherefore, the amount of money Antonella earned is **$450**."
