[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 49/100 path 3/3 answer="First, calculate the commission from selling $1000 worth of goods:\nCommission from $1000 sales = 30% * $1000 = $300\n\nNext, calculate the commission from the part of sales over $1000:\nAdditional commission from above $1000 sales = 10% * ($1000 + $1000) = 10% * $2000 = $200\n\nNow add both parts together to find Antonella's total earnings:\nTotal earnings = Commission from $1000 sales + Additional commission from part over $1000 sales\nTotal earnings = $300 + $200 = $500\n\nSo the amount of money Antonella earned is $500."
