[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 52/100 path 3/3 answer='First, calculate the total cost of the boots at both platforms:\n\nAmazon:\nCost of boots: $16\nShipping cost: $4\n\nTotal cost at Amazon: $16 + $4 = $20\n\nEbay:\nCost of boots: $13\nShipping cost (twice as much as Amazon): $4 * 2 = $8\n\nTotal cost at eBay: $13 + $8 = $21\n\nNow, find the difference between the total costs at eBay and Amazon:\n\nDifference: $21 - $20 = $1\n\nSo, the boots would be $1 more expensive on eBay.'
