[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 55/100 path 2/3 answer="To find out how many miles Alisa and Stanley biked in total, we need to calculate the distance each person covered separately and then add them together.\n\nAlisa's distance:\nDistance = Speed × Time\n   = 12 mph × 4.5 hrs\n   = 54 miles\n\nStanley's distance:\nDistance = Speed × Time\n   = 10 mph × 2.5 hrs\n   = 25 miles\n\nTotal distance biked by both:\nDistance_alisa + Distance_stanley\n     = 54 miles + 25 miles\n     = 79 miles\n\nTherefore, Alisa and Stanley biked a total of 79 miles."
