[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 55/100 path 3/3 answer="First, let's calculate how far Alisa traveled:\n\nAlisa's speed was 12 miles per hour for 4.5 hours.\nDistance Alisa biked = Speed × Time = 12 mph × 4.5 h = 54 miles\n\nNext, let's calculate how far Stanley traveled:\n\nStanley's speed was 10 miles per hour for 2.5 hours.\nDistance Stanley biked = Speed × Time = 10 mph × 2.5 h = 25 miles\n\nNow, let's find the total distance Alisa and Stanley biked together:\n\nTotal distance = Distance Alisa biked + Distance Stanley biked\nTotal distance = 54 miles + 25 miles = 79 miles\n\nSo, Alisa and Stanley biked a total of 79 miles."
