[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 56/100 path 1/3 answer='First, we calculate the total number of class sessions John attends:\n\n4 sessions/week * 6 weeks = 24 sessions\n\nNext, we calculate the total class time spent:\n\n2 hours/session * 24 sessions = 48 hours\n\nNow, we determine how many new recipes John learns:\n\n48 hours / 1.5 hours/recipe = 32 recipes\n\nSo, John learns 32 new recipes over the course of 6 weeks at the cooking class.'
