s the number of students who like to play video games. Rearranging gives us:\n\n\\( x = 35 - 15 = 20 \\)\n\nSo, 20 students like to play video games. This doesn't account for those who like both video games and music, which would increase the total number of students liking to play music from 17.5 to 19.5, but it also increases the total amount they can spend on their music-related activities, which might not make sense given the context of buying a specific item. Therefore, the adjusted calculation suggests 20 students like to play video games, leaving room for additional spending on other activities, possibly beyond what is required to buy the wallet.": 1}
