[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 65/100 path 2/3 answer='Henry needs 57 cars, and since each car requires 4 wheels, he will need 57 * 4 = <<57*4=228>>228 wheels for the cars.\nHe also needs 73 motorcycles, and each motorcycle requires 2 wheels, so he will need 73 * 2 = <<73*2=146>>146 wheels for the motorcycles.\nIn total, Henry needs 228 + 146 = <<228+146=374>>374 wheels for all the toys.\nIf he has a box with 650 wheels in it, and we want to find out how many wheels will be left over, we subtract the number needed from the number on hand: 650 - 374 = <<650-374=276>>276.\nTherefore, there will be 276 wheels left over.'
