[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 67/100 path 2/3 answer='First, calculate the cost for each type of fruit separately:\n\nFor peaches:\nWinston picked 6 pounds at $2.00 per pound, so the total cost is:\n\\( 6 \\text{ pounds} \\times \\$2.00/\\text{pound} = \\$12.00 \\)\n\nFor plums:\nWinston picked 8 pounds at $1.00 per pound, so the total cost is:\n\\( 8 \\text{ pounds} \\times \\$1.00/\\text{pound} = \\$8.00 \\)\n\nFor apricots:\nWinston picked 6 pounds at $3.00 per pound, so the total cost is:\n\\( 6 \\text{ pounds} \\times \\$3.00/\\text{pound} = \\$18.00 \\)\n\nNow, add up all the costs:\nTotal spent = Cost for peaches + Cost for plums + Cost for apricots\n\\( \\$12.00 + \\$8.00 + \\$18.00 = \\$38.00 \\)\n\nTherefore, Winston spent a total of $38.00 on fruit.'
