[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 68/100 start id=gsm8k_test_810
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 68/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 68/100 path 1/3 answer="To determine the number of additional students who joined during the summer months (May, June, July, August), we'll first calculate the total number of students on campus over those months. We start with 10 students at the beginning of the year, and double it each month:\n\n- Month 1: 10 students + 10 students = 20 students\n- Month 2: 20 students + 10 students = 30 students\n- Month 3: 30 students + 10 students = 40 students\n\nAdding these up gives us the total number of students on campus by the end of June:\n20 students (Month 1) + 30 students (Month 2) + 40 students (Month 3) = 90 students\n\nNow, we subtract the initial number of students from the total number of students by the end of the year (December):\nTotal students by the end of December - Initial students = Additional students above and beyond the ones already on campus\n90 students - 10 students = 80 students\n\nTherefore, there are 80 additional students who joined the campus by the end of May compared to the original number of students at the beginning of the year."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 68/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 68/100 path 2/3 answer='To find out how many additional students joined by the end of May compared to the initial number, we can follow these steps:\n\n1. Determine the total number of months from January to May.\n   \\[\n   \\text{Number of months} = 5 - 1 = 4\n   \\]\n\n2. Calculate the total number of students who joined during each month:\n   - January: \\(10\\) (initial)\n   - February: \\(10 \\times 2 = 20\\)\n   - March: \\(10 \\times 2^2 = 40\\)\n   - April: \\(10 \\times 2^3 = 80\\)\n   - May: \\(10 \\times 2^4 = 160\\)\n\n3. Sum up all the students who joined during the entire period:\n   \\[\n   10 + 20 + 40 + 80 + 160 = 310\n   \\]\n\nSo, the additional number of students who joined by the end of May over and above the number of students already on campus at the beginning of the year was **310**.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 68/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 68/100 path 3/3 answer='110'
