yond the ones already on campus\n90 students - 10 students = 80 students\n\nTherefore, there are 80 additional students who joined the campus by the end of May compared to the original number of students at the beginning of the year.": 1, 'To find out how many additional students joined by the end of May compared to the initial number, we can follow these steps:\n\n1. Determine the total number of months from January to May.\n   \\[\n   \\text{Number of months} = 5 - 1 = 4\n   \\]\n\n2. Calculate the total number of students who joined during each month:\n   - January: \\(10\\) (initial)\n   - February: \\(10 \\times 2 = 20\\)\n   - March: \\(10 \\times 2^2 = 40\\)\n   - April: \\(10 \\times 2^3 = 80\\)\n   - May: \\(10 \\times 2^4 = 160\\)\n\n3. Sum up all the students who joined during the entire period:\n   \\[\n   10 + 20 + 40 + 80 + 160 = 310\n   \\]\n\nSo, the additional number of students who joined by the end of May over and above the number of students already on campus at the beginning of the year was **310**.': 1, '110': 1}
