                 = $0.8 - $0.5 = $0.3 per lollipop\n\nTherefore, the profit from selling all 300 lollipops is:\nProfit = Total lollipops sold × Profit per lollipop\n        = 300 lollipops × $0.3/lollipop\n        = $90\n\nFinally, we multiply the profit by the number of students to find the class's total earnings:\n\nClass total earnings = Profit × Number of students\n                     = $90 × 30 students\n                     = $2700\n\nThus, the class raised $2700 from the sale of lollipops.": 1, "To find out how much money the class raised from selling lollipops, we first calculate the total number of lollipops sold by all students. Each of the 30 students sold 10 lollipops on average, so together they sold \\(30 \\times 10\\) lollipops. Then, since each lollipop was sold for $0.8, the total amount of money collected is \\(30 \\times 10 \\times 0.8\\).\n\nLet's do the math:\n\\[ \\text{Total Lollipops Sold} = 30 \\times 10 = 300 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Total Money Collected} = 300 \\times 0.8 = \\$240 \\]\n\nSince they bought the lollipops at $0.5 each, the money raised can also be calculated as \\(240 \\div 0.5\\).\n\nLet's perform the second calculation:\n\\[ \\text{Money Raised} = \\frac{\\$240}{\\$0.5} = \\$480 \\]\n\nSo, the class raised a total of $480 from the sale of lollipops. The question asks specifically about raising money for a class fund, so no additional amounts would be mentioned beyond what was initially asked (raising $480). Therefore, the final answer aligns with the original example's explanation without needing to repeat the specific details provided in the example.": 1}
