[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 1/3 answer="First, we'll find out how many Junebugs were removed each day:\nMonday: 39 bugs\nTuesday and Wednesday: Twice as many as Monday, so 39 * 2 = 78 bugs\n\nAdding these up gives us a total of 39 + 78 = 117 bugs.\n\nNow, we know the total number of bugs removed was 57 (Friday) plus 48 (Thursday), which equals 105 bugs.\n\nTo find the average number of bugs removed per day, we divide the total number of bugs by the number of days:\n\nAverage = Total Bugs / Number of Days\nAverage = 105 / 6\nAverage = 17.5\n\nSo the average number of Junebugs that Rita removes per day is 17.5."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 2/3 answer='First, we calculate the total number of Junebugs removed from Monday to Thursday:\n- Monday: 39 bugs\n- Tuesday: 39 * 2 = 78 bugs\n- Wednesday: 39 * 2 = 78 bugs\n\nNow, we sum these up to find the total number of bugs removed:\n39 + 78 + 78 + 48 + 57 = 290 bugs\n\nTo find the average number of bugs removed per day, we divide the total number of bugs by the number of days (which is 5):\n290 / 5 = 58 bugs per day\n\nTherefore, the average number of Junebugs that Rita removes per day is 58.'
