[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 80/100 start id=gsm8k_test_1093
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 80/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 80/100 path 1/3 answer='First, calculate the total area of the walls:\nNorth wall: \\(10 \\text{ ft} \\times 8 \\text{ ft} = 80 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\nSouth wall: \\(10 \\text{ ft} \\times 8 \\text{ ft} = 80 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\nEast wall: \\(5 \\text{ ft} \\times 8 \\text{ ft} = 40 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\nWest wall: \\(5 \\text{ ft} \\times 8 \\text{ ft} = 40 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\n\nTotal area: \\(80 + 80 + 40 + 40 = 240 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\n\nNow, calculate how many gallons of paint are needed:\n\\(240 \\text{ sq ft} \\div 20 \\text{ sq ft/gallon} = 12 \\text{ gallons}\\)\n\nFinally, calculate the total cost:\n\\(12 \\text{ gallons} \\times \\$12/\\text{gallon} = \\$144\\)\n\nIt will cost $144 to paint the room.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 80/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 80/100 path 2/3 answer='144'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 80/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 80/100 path 3/3 answer="First, calculate the total area of the walls: north wall (10 feet) + south wall (10 feet) + east wall (8 feet) + west wall (8 feet) = 36 square feet.\nThen, subtract the area already covered by the walls to find the remaining uncovered area: 36 square feet - 20 square feet = 16 square feet uncovered.\nNow, divide the uncovered area by the coverage rate to find out how many gallons of paint are needed: 16 square feet / 20 square feet per gallon = 0.8 gallons.\nSince you can't buy a fraction of a gallon, round up to the nearest whole number to get 1 gallon of paint needed. Finally, multiply the number of gallons by the price per gallon ($12): 1 gallon * $12/gallon = $12.\nTherefore, it will cost $12 to paint the room."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 80/100 done id=gsm8k_test_1093 prediction='First, calculate the total area of the walls:\nNorth wall: \\(10 \\text{ ft} \\times 8 \\text{ ft} = 80 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\nSouth wall: \\(10 \\text{ ft} \\times 8 \\text{ ft} = 80 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\nEast wall: \\(5 \\text{ ft} \\times 8 \\text{ ft} = 40 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\nWest wall: \\(5 \\text{ ft} \\times 8 \\text{ ft} = 40 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\n\nTotal area: \\(80 + 80 + 40 + 40 = 240 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\n\nNow, calculate how many gallons of paint are needed:\n\\(240 \\text{ sq ft} \\div 20 \\text{ sq ft/gallon} = 12 \\text{ gallons}\\)\n\nFinally, calculate the total cost:\n\\(12 \\text{ gallons} \\times \\$12/\\text{gallon} = \\$144\\)\n\nIt will cost $144 to paint the room.' gold='144' correct=False vote_counts={'First, calculate the total area of the walls:\nNorth wall: \\(10 \\text{ ft} \\times 8 \\text{ ft} = 80 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\nSouth wall: \\(10 \\text{ ft} \\times 8 \\text{ ft} = 80 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\nEast wall: \\(5 \\text{ ft} \\times 8 \\text{ ft} = 40 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\nWest wall: \\(5 \\text{ ft} \\times 8 \\text{ ft} = 40 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\n\nTotal area: \\(80 + 80 + 40 + 40 = 240 \\text{ sq ft}\\)\n\nNow, calculate how many gallons of paint are needed:\n\\(240 \\text{ sq ft} \\div 20 \\text{ sq ft/gallon} = 12 \\text{ gallons}\\)\n\nFinally, calculate the total cost:\n\\(12 \\text{ gallons} \\times \\$12/\\text{gallon} = \\$144\\)\n\nIt will cost $144 to paint the room.': 1, '144': 1, "First, calculate the total area of the walls: north wall (10 feet) + south wall (10 feet) + east wall (8 feet) + west wall (8 feet) = 36 square feet.\nThen, subtract the area already covered by the walls to find the remaining uncovered area: 36 square feet - 20 square feet = 16 square feet uncovered.\nNow, divide the uncovered area by the coverage rate to find out how many gallons of paint are needed: 16 square feet / 20 square feet per gallon = 0.8 gallons.\nSince you can't buy a fraction of a gallon, round up to the nearest whole number to get 1 gallon of paint needed. Finally, multiply the number of gallons by the price per gallon ($12): 1 gallon * $12/gallon = $12.\nTherefore, it will cost $12 to paint the room.": 1}
