[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 81/100 path 1/3 answer="To find out how old Jeff is, we start with the information given:\n\n1. Martha is 4 years younger than Mike.\n   So, if Mike is 24 years old, Martha is:\n   24 - 4 = 20 years old.\n\n2. Jeff is 10 years older than Martha.\n   Therefore, Jeff's age is:\n   20 + 10 = 30 years old.\n\nSo, Jeff is 30 years old."
