[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 84/100 path 1/3 answer='First, we calculate how many full boxes of 8 crayons can be made from 200 crayons:\n\\[ \\text{Number of boxes} = \\frac{200}{8} = 25 \\]\n\nEach crayon weighs 1 ounce, so the number of crayons used would also be equal to 25 (since each box contains one crayon):\n\\[ \\text{Number of crayons} = 25 \\]\n\nNext, we convert the number of crayons to ounces:\n\\[ \\text{Total crayon weight} = 25 \\times 1 \\text{ ounce/crayon} = 25 \\text{ ounces} \\]\n\nNow, we know that each box weighs 8 ounces, so the total weight of the crayons is:\n\\[ \\text{Total crayon weight} = 25 \\text{ ounces} \\]\n\nTo find out the total weight of the boxes, we multiply the total weight of the crayons by the number of boxes:\n\\[ \\text{Total weight of boxes} = 25 \\text{ ounces/box} \\times 16 \\text{ ounces/package} = 400 \\text{ ounces} \\]\n\nFinally, we convert the total weight of the boxes from ounces to pounds:\n\\[ \\text{Total weight of boxes} = 400 \\text{ ounces} \\div 16 \\text{ ounces/pound} = 25 \\text{ pounds} \\]\n\nSo the total weight of the crayons and the boxes when there are 16 ounces to a pound is 25 pounds.'
