[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 88/100 path 1/3 answer="To solve this problem, let's break it down into steps:\n\n1) First, we need to find out how many books Bob can purchase with his total budget of $27,000:\n   27,000 / 500 = 54 books\n\n2) Now we know that each book costs $500. To find out how many books Bob can buy per school, we divide the number of books he can purchase by the number of schools:\n   54 books / 3 schools = 18 books per school\n\nTherefore, Bob can buy 18 books per school with his available funds."
