[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 90/100 path 1/3 answer="First, let's calculate the amount of water removed per day at each setting:\n\nLow setting:\n1 liter per day\n\nMedium setting:\n2 liters per day (twice as much as the low setting)\n\nHigh setting:\n4 liters per day (twice as much as the medium setting)\n\nNow we can calculate the total amount of water removed over the 9 days:\n\nLow settings: 9 days × 1 liter/day = 9 liters\nMedium settings: 9 days × 2 liters/day = 18 liters\nHigh settings: 9 days × 4 liters/day = 36 liters\n\nTotal water removed:\n9 + 18 + 36 = 63 liters\n\nSo, the dehumidifier removed a total of 63 liters of water from the air in Brian's basement."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 90/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 90/100 path 2/3 answer="To calculate the total amount of water removed by the dehumidifier over the given period:\n\nLow setting:\n- Daily removal: 1 liter\n\nMedium setting (twice as much as low):\n- Daily removal: 1 liter × 2 = 2 liters\n\nHigh setting (twice as much as medium):\n- Daily removal: 2 liters × 2 = 4 liters\n\nTotal daily removal: 1 liter + 2 liters + 4 liters = 7 liters/day\n\nFor 3 days with low setting:\n- Total removal: 7 liters/day × 3 days = 21 liters\n\nFor 3 days with medium setting:\n- Total removal: 7 liters/day × 3 days = 21 liters\n\nFor 5 days with high setting:\n- Total removal: 7 liters/day × 5 days = 35 liters\n\nAdding all these up gives us the total removal:\n- Total removal: 21 liters (low) + 21 liters (medium) + 35 liters (high) = 77 liters\n\nTherefore, the dehumidifier removed a total of 77 liters of water from the air in Brian's basement."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 90/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 90/100 path 3/3 answer="To calculate the total amount of water the dehumidifier removed over the given period, we'll first determine how much water it removed each setting:\n\n1. Low setting:\n1 liter/day × 3 days = 3 liters\n\n2. Medium setting:\n2 times the low setting (since it's double the amount):\n2 × 3 liters = 6 liters\n\n3. High setting:\n2 times the medium setting (since it's double the amount):\n2 × 6 liters = 12 liters\n\nNow, let's sum up all the amounts:\nLow setting: 3 liters\nMedium setting: 6 liters\nHigh setting: 12 liters\n\nTotal amount of water removed = 3 + 6 + 12 = 21 liters\n\nTherefore, the total amount of water the dehumidifier removed from the air in Brian's basement is 21 liters."
