[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 94/100 path 1/3 answer="To calculate how much dog food the kennel house will need in a week, we first determine the daily consumption for both types of dogs:\n\n- Each German Shepherd consumes 5 kg/day.\n- Each Bulldog consumes 3 kg/day.\n\nFor the German Shepherds:\n- They have 3 dogs, so together they consume 5 kg/dog × 3 dogs = 15 kg/day.\n\nFor the Bulldogs:\n- They also have 2 dogs, so together they consume 3 kg/dog × 2 dogs = 6 kg/day.\n\nNow we add these two amounts together to get the total weekly consumption:\n- Total daily consumption = 15 kg (German Shepherds) + 6 kg (Bulldogs) = 21 kg/day.\n\nFinally, to find out how much dog food they'll need in a week:\n- Weekly consumption = 21 kg/day × 7 days/week = 147 kg/week.\n\nTherefore, the kennel house will need 147 kilograms of dog food in a week."
