[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 96/100 path 1/3 answer="First, let's calculate how many days Josh is available to service cars each week:\n\n- There are 7 days in a workweek.\n- Except Sunday and Wednesday, Josh works 5 days (Monday through Friday).\n\nSo, on weekdays (Monday through Friday), he can service:\n\\( 5 \\text{ days} \\times 3 \\text{ cars/day} = 15 \\text{ cars} \\)\n\nOn Saturday and Sunday, he doesn't have a car to service, so those days he only serves:\n\\( 2 \\text{ days} \\times 3 \\text{ cars/day} = 6 \\text{ cars} \\)\n\nNow, we add up all the cars he can service during the week:\n\\( 15 \\text{ cars} + 6 \\text{ cars} = 21 \\text{ cars} \\)\n\nSince he gets paid $4 per car, his weekly earnings would be:\n\\( 21 \\text{ cars} \\times \\$4/\\text{car} = \\$<<21*4=84>>84 \\)\n\nTo find out how much he makes in 2 weeks, we multiply his weekly earnings by 2:\n\\( \\$84/\\text{week} \\times 2\\text{ weeks} = \\$<<84*2=168>>168 \\)\n\nTherefore, Josh makes $168 in 2 weeks."
