[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 97/100 path 3/3 answer="Let's break down the problem step-by-step:\n\n1. Randy starts with:\n   - 9 oatmeal cookies\n   - 4 chocolate chip cookies\n   - 5 sugar cookies\n\n2. He eats 3 cookies for an early snack, one of each flavor:\n   - Oatmeal cookies eaten: 3 (one of each flavor)\n   - Chocolate chip cookies eaten: 3 (one of each flavor)\n   - Sugar cookies eaten: 3 (one of each flavor)\n\n3. For lunch, he gives away 2 oatmeal cookies:\n   - Remaining oatmeal cookies: 9 - 2 = 7 oatmeal cookies\n\n4. He bakes 4 of each flavor for dinner:\n   - Oatmeal cookies baked: 4\n   - Chocolate chip cookies baked: 4\n   - Sugar cookies baked: 4\n\nNow let's calculate the total number of cookies Randy has left:\n\n- Oatmeal cookies: 7\n- Chocolate chip cookies: 4\n- Sugar cookies: 4\n- Remaining cookies: 7 + 4 + 4 = 15\n\nSo, Randy now has **15** cookies in total."
