[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 98/100 path 1/3 answer="First, let's find out how much each person raised:\n\nKim raised $320 more than Alexandra, so Kim raised $430 (Alexandra's amount) + $320 = $750.\n\nMaryam raised $400 more than Sarah, so Maryam raised $300 (Sarah's amount) + $400 = $700.\n\nNow, let's calculate the total amount raised by all four individuals:\n\nKim raised $750,\nAlexandra raised $430,\nMaryam raised $700,\nand Sarah raised $300.\n\nAdding these amounts together gives us:\n$750 + $430 + $700 + $300 = $2,380.\n\nTherefore, they all raised a total of $2,380."
