[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 35/100 path 1/3 answer="To solve this problem step-by-step:\n\n### Step 1: Analyze the given equations\n\nGiven:\n\\[\na(a+2b) = \\frac{104}{3}, \\quad b(b+2c) = \\frac{7}{9}, \\quad c(c+2a) = -7\n\\]\n\n### Step 2: Express each variable as \\( x \\)\n\nLet's set:\n\\[\na = x - y, \\quad b = x + z, \\quad c = y + w\n\\]\nwhere \\( x, y, z, w \\in \\mathbb{Z} \\).\n\nSubstitute these into the original equations to get:\n\\[\n(x - y)((x - y) + 2z) = \\frac{104}{3}\n\\]\n\\[\n(x + z)((x + z) + 2w) = \\frac{7}{9}\n\\]\n\\[\n(y + w)(y + w + 2x) = -7\n\\]\n\n### Step 3: Simplify each equation\n\nFirst equation simplifies to:\n\\[\n(x - y)^2 + 2xz = \\frac{104}{3}\n\\]\n\nSecond equation simplifies to:\n\\[\n(x + z)^2 + 2zw = \\frac{7}{9}\n\\]\n\nThird equation simplifies to:\n\\[\n(y + w)^2 + 2wy = -7\n\\]\n\n### Step 4: Iterate to find integer solutions\n\nWe need to find integers \\( x, y, z, w \\) that satisfy all three equations simultaneously. Let's try some values for \\( x, y, z, w \\):\n\n#### Try \\( x = 4, y = 0, z = 1, w = -2 \\):\n\\[\na = 4 - 1"
