ectly correlate with the performance of the algorithm used to minimize the MSE.\n\n   - **Statement C**: "it does not matter whether half is there or not."\n     - This is actually a contradiction. If we don\'t include half, the formula would still apply perfectly. Including half means we\'re adding another variable that could potentially affect the calculation, but it\'s not necessary for the MSE computation itself.\n\n   - **Statement D**: "none of the above"\n     - This is a correct': 1, 'D': 1}
