[zero_shot][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 9/100 done id=mmlu_validation_142 prediction='To solve this, we need to calculate the daily intake of creatine based on the given weight (70 kg) and the recommended loading dose (one week).\n\nStep 1: Convert kilograms to grams.\n\\[ 70 \\text{ kg} = 70 \\times 1000 \\text{ g} = 70,000 \\text{ g} \\]\n\nStep 2: Calculate the total daily intake needed for one week.\nSince there are 7 days in a week, multiply the daily intake by 7.\n\\[ \\text{Total weekly intake} = 70,000 \\text{ g/day} \\times 7 \\text{ days/week} = 490,000 \\text{ g/week} \\]\n\nStep 3: Divide the total weekly intake by the number of days in a week to find the daily intake.\n\\[ \\text{Daily intake} = \\frac{490,000 \\text{ g}}{7 \\text{ days}} = 70,000 \\text{ g/day} \\]\n\nStep 4: Compare with the provided choices.\nThe closest value among the options is C. 10' gold='D' correct=False
