[zero_shot][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 43/100 done id=mmlu_validation_592 prediction='To determine which options represent continuous data, we need to understand what continuous data means. Continuous data can take on any value within a range or interval.\n\n1. **I. The speed your car goes**: Speed is typically measured in meters per second (m/s), kilometers per hour (km/h), etc., which can have decimal values. This is continuous data because it can vary infinitely between any two points.\n\n2. **II. The number of outcomes of a binomial experiment**: A binomial experiment involves fixed parameters like n (number of trials) and p (probability of success). The number of possible outcomes depends on these parameters but is still countable and finite. Therefore, this is discrete data.\n\n3. **III. The average temperature in San Francisco**: Temperature is usually measured in degrees Celsius or Fahrenheit, which can have decimal values. Average temperatures can also vary continuously over time. Thus, this is continuous data.\n\n4. **IV. The wingspan of a bird**: Wingspan is generally measured in units like centimeters or inches, which can have decimal values. It can vary continuously based on individual differences among birds. Hence, this is continuous data.\n\n5. **V. The jersey numbers of a football team**: Jersey numbers are assigned numerically from' gold='A' correct=False
