[zero_shot][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 80/100 done id=mmlu_validation_1301 prediction="The question involves understanding the nature of an offer made by Water Works and how it affects the entitlement of Farber based on his suggestion being accepted.\n\nStep 1: Analyze the initial offer.\n- Water Works offered $100 for each suggestion actually used.\n- This means the offer was conditional upon the actual use of the suggestion.\n\nStep 2: Consider the change in the offer.\n- After the decision to increase the award to $500, the offer became unconditional.\n- Now, regardless of whether the suggestion is used or not, Water Works agrees to pay $500.\n\nStep 3: Evaluate Farber's situation.\n- Farber's suggestion was accepted two days before the public announcement of the increased award.\n- At that point, the offer was still conditional ($100 per suggestion).\n- However, when the announcement came out, the offer became unconditional ($500).\n\nStep 4: Determine Farber's entitlement.\n- Since the suggestion was accepted before the announcement, he should have been paid according to the original condition (conditional $100 per suggestion).\n- When the announcement came out, the offer changed from conditional to unconditional, but the payment has already been made.\n\nTherefore, Farber is entitled to:\n\nThe answer" gold='C' correct=False
