[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 13/100 path 3/3 answer="Let's denote:\n- \\( R \\) as the price of one red car,\n- \\( F \\) as the price of one action figure,\n- \\( D \\) as the price of one doll,\n\nWe know from the problem statement:\n\\[ R = \\$4 \\]\n\\[ D = 3F + R \\]\n\\[ F = \\$5 \\]\n\nFirst, we substitute the value of \\( R \\) into the equation for \\( D \\):\n\\[ D = 3(\\$5) + \\$4 \\]\n\\[ D = \\$15 + \\$4 \\]\n\\[ D = \\$19 \\]\n\nNow, we can find the total value of all toys combined:\nTotal Value = (Number of Red Cars × Price per Red Car) + (Number of Action Figures × Price per Action Figure) + (Number of Dolls × Price per Doll)\n\\[ Total\\ Value = (5R) + (3F) + (D) \\]\n\\[ Total\\ Value = (5 \\times \\$4) + (3 \\times \\$5) + \\$19 \\]\n\\[ Total\\ Value = (\\$20) + (\\$15) + \\$19 \\]\n\\[ Total\\ Value = \\$54 \\]\n\nTherefore, the total value of all toys is $54."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 13/100 done id=gsm8k_test_163 prediction='33' gold='50' correct=False vote_counts={'33': 1, '34': 1, "Let's denote:\n- \\( R \\) as the price of one red car,\n- \\( F \\) as the price of one action figure,\n- \\( D \\) as the price of one doll,\n\nWe know from the problem statement:\n\\[ R = \\$4 \\]\n\\[ D = 3F + R \\]\n\\[ F = \\$5 \\]\n\nFirst, we substitute the value of \\( R \\) into the equation for \\( D \\):\n\\[ D = 3(\\$5) + \\$4 \\]\n\\[ D = \\$15 + \\$4 \\]\n\\[ D = \\$19 \\]\n\nNow, we can find the total value of all toys combined:\nTotal Value = (Number of Red Cars × Price per Red Car) + (Number of Action Figures × Price per Action Figure) + (Number of Dolls × Price per Doll)\n\\[ Total\\ Value = (5R) + (3F) + (D) \\]\n\\[ Total\\ Value = (5 \\times \\$4) + (3 \\times \\$5) + \\$19 \\]\n\\[ Total\\ Value = (\\$20) + (\\$15) + \\$19 \\]\n\\[ Total\\ Value = \\$54 \\]\n\nTherefore, the total value of all toys is $54.": 1}
