[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 27/100 path 2/3 answer="To find out how many guns each person would have if they shared them equally, we first need to calculate the total number of guns.\n\nTotal guns = DJ's guns + Nick's guns + RJ's guns + Richard's guns\n\nTotal guns = 8 + 10 + 1 + 5\n\nTotal guns = 24\n\nNow, to find out how many guns each person would have if they shared equally:\n\nGuns per person = Total guns ÷ Number of people\n\nGuns per person = 24 ÷ 4\n\nGuns per person = 6\n\nEach person would have 6 guns if they shared them equally."
