[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 37/100 path 1/3 answer='If there were two balloons before the price increase, they would have a combined total cost of $900 / 20 = $<|avg_total_cost_per_balloon|> per balloon on the original day.\nAfter the price increase, these balloons would now cost a total of (|avg_total_cost_per_balloon| + 20) * 2 = $<|total_cost_increase|> per balloon.\nIn total, the balloons cost $<|total_cost_increase|> * 170 = $12, 500 after the price increase.\n\nTherefore, Bentley paid $12, 500 to fill 170 balloons with the price increase applied.'
