[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 71/100 path 3/3 answer='We start with 600 burritos distributed among 50 students, with each student receiving 10 burritos. So the total number of burritos given out initially is:\n\n\\[ 50 \\text{ students} \\times 10 \\text{ burritos/student} = 500 \\text{ burritos} \\]\n\nMr. George eats 20 of these burritos, so we subtract those from the initial distribution:\n\n\\[ 500 \\text{ burritos} - 20 \\text{ burritos} = 480 \\text{ burritos} \\]\n\nAfter distributing all the burritos and accounting for the ones Mr. George ate, we have 480 burritos left. Thus, the total number of leftover burritos from the picnic is:\n\n\\[ \\boxed{480} \\]'
